<div class="container">
    <h1>⬇️ Installing Visual Studio 2022 for .NET Development</h1>

    <p>
        Before we can start building applications, we first need to install the right tools. 
        In this section, we will walk you through installing 
        <strong>Visual Studio 2022 (Community Edition)</strong> along with the necessary 
        .NET components.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>📥 Step 1: Download Visual Studio 2022</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Go to the official website: <a href="https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/" target="_blank">Visual Studio Downloads</a>.</li>
        <li>Select <strong>Visual Studio 2022 Community Edition</strong> (free for students & individuals).</li>
        <li>Download and run the installer file (<code>vs_installer.exe</code>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>⚙️ Step 2: Select Workloads</h2>
    <p>
        When the installer opens, you’ll need to select the workloads (features) you want.  
        For this course, make sure you check the following options:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>✅ <strong>ASP.NET and web development</strong> (required for web apps).</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>.NET multi-platform app UI development</strong> (for cross-platform apps).</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>.NET desktop development</strong> (for Windows desktop apps).</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Data storage and processing</strong> (for working with databases).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>📦 Step 3: Add Required Components</h2>
    <p>Make sure the following components are included during installation:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>.NET 9.0 Runtime & SDK</strong> (required).</li>
        <li><strong>Entity Framework Core tools</strong> (recommended for database work).</li>
        <li><strong>SQL Server Express 2019 LocalDB</strong> (optional lightweight database).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>📍 Step 4: Install & Launch</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Click <strong>Install</strong> to begin.</li>
        <li>Wait for the installation to complete (may take 10–30 minutes).</li>
        <li>Once finished, open <strong>Visual Studio 2022</strong>.</li>
        <li>(Optional) Sign in with a Microsoft account to sync settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>✅ Step 5: Verify .NET Installation</h2>
    <p>To confirm .NET is installed, open <code>Command Prompt</code> or <code>PowerShell</code> and run:</p>
    <pre><code>dotnet --version</code></pre>
    <p>You should see something like <code>9.0.x</code>, which means .NET 9 is installed successfully.</p>

